dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Suwalki, sheet K-17. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Suwalki, Poland. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Germany 1:25,000. German General Staff 1925-36; Germany, 1:100,000, German General Staff, Sheet 30B, 1935; Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, sheets 32-35, 1931; 32-36, 1929; 33-35, 1931 and 33-36, 1929. Road classification in Poland based on British intelligence reports, 1943.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
